# ========================================
# SB Knowledge Search - Environment Variables
# ========================================
#
# Copy this file to .dev.vars for local development
# For production, use: wrangler secret put <KEY_NAME>
#
# DO NOT commit .dev.vars with actual secrets!
# ========================================

# ========================================
# REQUIRED: OpenAI API Configuration
# ========================================

# OpenAI API Key
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Format: sk-proj-... (starts with "sk-proj-" for project keys)
# or sk-... (for legacy keys)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-your-openai-api-key-here

# ========================================
# OPTIONAL: Cloudflare AI Gateway
# ========================================

# AI Gateway Base URL (for request caching, logging, and rate limiting)
# Get your gateway URL from: https://developers.cloudflare.com/ai-gateway/
# Format: https://gateway.ai.cloudflare.com/v1/{account_id}/{gateway_name}/openai
# GATEWAY_BASE_URL=https://gateway.ai.cloudflare.com/v1/your-account-id/your-gateway-name/openai

# ========================================
# CLOUDFLARE BINDINGS (configured in wrangler.jsonc)
# ========================================
# These are NOT environment variables - they're Cloudflare bindings
# configured in wrangler.jsonc and available via env.* in your code
#
# Currently configured bindings:
# - env.AI (Cloudflare Workers AI binding for AI Search)
# - env.Chat (Durable Object for chat state management)
#
# AI Search AutoRAG Sources:
# - sbknowledge-test (SuperBenefit general knowledge)
# - sbgov-test (SuperBenefit governance documentation)
#
# These must be created in your Cloudflare account separately
# ========================================

# ========================================
# NOTES FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
# ========================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .dev.vars:
#    cp .env.example .dev.vars
#
# 2. Fill in your actual OpenAI API key in .dev.vars
#
# 3. Start the dev server:
#    npm run dev
#
# 4. The Cloudflare AI binding will work automatically
#    in local development mode
#
# ========================================

# ========================================
# NOTES FOR PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# ========================================
#
# 1. Set secrets using Wrangler CLI:
#    wrangler secret put OPENAI_API_KEY
#
# 2. Or bulk upload from .dev.vars:
#    wrangler secret bulk .dev.vars
#
# 3. Ensure AutoRAG sources exist:
#    - sbknowledge-test
#    - sbgov-test
#
# 4. Deploy:
#    npm run deploy
#
# ========================================
